HEADWORD: guppy
<hw>guppy</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after <person>R. J. L.
<etsep>Guppy</etsep></person>, who brought speciments to the British
museum. <au>RHUD</au>]</ety> <def>A small freshwater fish of South
America and West Indies (<spn>Lebistes reticulatus</spn> or
<spn>Poecilia reticulata</spn>, originaly called <spn>Gerardinus
guppyi</spn>), often kept in aquariums; also called <altname>rainbow
fish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> rainbow fish, <spn>Lebistes
reticulatus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

